Title: Update booking using invalid data returns wrong error response

Description: If user sends a PUT request to update a booking by booking ID, using invalid data. API returns wrong error status code and message

Steps to reproduce:
    1. Send a POST request to create a booking
    2. Fetch booking ID
    3. Send a PUT request to update created booking by booking ID using invalid data (missing email, phone, etc)
    4. Verify response

Expected: 400 status code and meaningful error message (like for creating booking with invalid data, check /features/negative/CreateBooking.feature)

Actual: 401 "Unauthorized" status code and empty response body

Screen recording: https://imgur.com/a/eTRo0pG

Example json payload:
{
  "bookingid": 444,
  "roomid": 444,
  "lastname": "Phelipeau",
  "depositpaid": true,
  "email": "tphelipeau0@constantcontact.com",
  "phone": "+1234567825",
  "bookingdates": {
    "checkin": "2025-11-28",
    "checkout": "2025-12-04"
  }
}